content:
In January, the OSC <a href="https://www.osc.gov.on.ca/documents/en/Securities-Category2/csa_20200116_21-327_trading-crypto-assets.pdf" data-v-f87c67ca="">published additional guidance</a>, clarifying whether securities laws apply to crypto exchanges. At the time, the regulator said securities legislation might apply to crypto exchanges that facilitate the trading of crypto assets that are commodities, because users' contractual right to crypto-assets may itself constitute a derivative, a security or both.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
"Platforms would not generally be subject to securities legislation if each of the following apply: • the underlying crypto asset itself is not a security or derivative; and • the contract or instrument for the purchase, sale or delivery of a crypto asset," the OSC said at the time.&nbsp;
